    <bioghist>Political and social justice group in Benton Harbor, Mich., founded 2003 by Rev. Edward Pinkney, a Baptist minister. A 2005 recall election of a Benton Harbor city commissioner organized by Rev. Pinkney led to Pinkney's conviction on charges of election fraud, a conviction Pinkney's supporters saw as politically motivated, and his later imprisonment after cursing a judge with a curse from the Bible.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>CD-ROM copy (42 mb) of blog maintained by Rev. Pinkney and others (2005-2009) commenting on BANCO activities, Benton Harbor and Berrien County politics and economy, and Pinkney's legal troubles; also correspondence, religious writings, protest flyers, court and prison materials, and picket signs used in BANCO demonstrations, photos of demonstrations, clippings, flyers, t-shirts, and a DVD (60 min.) "What's going on in Benton Harbor? The trial of Reverend Pinkney."</scopecontent>
